            <statement>
            <p>
              If <m>m</m> is an odd integer,
              then <m>3m^2 + 7m + 12</m> is an even integer.
            </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
              <p>
                We assume that <m>m</m> is an odd integer and will prove that 
                <m>3m^2 + 7m + 12</m> is an even integer.  Since <m>m</m> is odd, there exists 
                an integer <m>k</m> such that <m>m = 2k +1</m>. Hence,
                <md>
                  <mrow>3m^2 + 7m + 12 \amp = 3 \left( 2k + 1 \right)^2 + 7 \left( 2k + 1 \right) + 12</mrow>
                  <mrow>\amp = 12k^2 + 26k + 22</mrow>
                  <mrow>\amp = 2 \left( 6k^2 + 13k + 11 \right)</mrow>
                </md>
                By the closure properties of the integers, <m>\left( 6k^2 + 13k + 11 \right)</m> 
                is an integer. Hence, this proves that if <m>m</m> is odd, then 
                <m>3m^2 + 7m + 12</m> is an even integer.
              </p>
            </answer>
          </task>
 
    </exercise>

